      <p class="eyebrow">Sidequest</p>
      <h1>Six Sines</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A compact synthesizer built around six sine sources and a flexible
        modulation matrix — small in footprint, surprisingly deep to patch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Six Sines is a free and open-source instrument I write and maintain. It
        keeps the signal path simple — six sine oscillators you route and
        modulate against each other — while leaving plenty of room to explore.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's cross-platform and available as a plugin in the usual formats. The
        source, releases, and issue tracker all live on GitHub.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Source &amp; releases: <a href="https://github.com/baconpaul/six-sines"
            >github.com/baconpaul/six-sines</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
